OL,5,Cleader
OL,7,FThere has been some controversy over
OL,8,FMr Gething receiving the backing of
OL,9,Fthe Unite union, after his opponent
OL,10,Fwas disqualified because he has never
OL,11,Fheld "elected lay office as
OL,12,Frepresentatives of workers".
OL,14,FMr Miles said it was "a new rule that
OL,15,Fno-one was aware of" and that members
OL,16,Fwere unhappy.
OL,18,FBut Unite said it had carried out the
OL,19,Fnomination process correctly and Mr
OL,20,FGething said it was up to the union to
OL,21,Fdetermine its own democratic processes.
